Coach Austine Eguavoen can get more out of Super Eagles midfielder Joe Aribo by playing him in the number 10 position at the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon, his teammate in Rangers FC Leon Balogun has stated. Balogun, who missed the tournament due to injury, stated this in an Instagram Live video on Monday. The Rangers star urged Eguavoen to deploy the 25-year-old in the number 10 role for the Super Eagles going forward. “I have always known he’s a great player, right from the time I started playing with him. He’s in great form this season and he managed to bring that to Nigeria in the last two games,” Balogun said in an Instagram Live video.   AFCON 2021: Aubameyang returns to Arsenal over health issues     Six top European coaches sacked in 2021/2022 season     Eguavoen to ring  changes against Guinea-Bissau   - Advertisement - “To me, he’s not playing in his best position. If you put him in as a No.10, he will give you more joy because he knows how to take on players, he knows how to delay the play in a way. “However, I’m happy he’s found a way to bring his form to the national team because I think people have been waiting for long, for him to actually replicate the kind of form he has at club level. “So, “I’ m actually happy he’s found a way to do it in a different position.”